size:
Oris Ocean Trilogy Set - a limited & numbered edition set of only 200 sets, with all 3 pieces sharing the same limited edition number. The trio of watches includes the: • Oris Blue Whale limited edition 200 pieces, available exclusively as part of the Oris Ocean Trilogy set).

• Oris Great Barrier Reef III limited edition 2000 pieces.

• Oris Clean Ocean limited edition 2000 pieces.

The set is delivered in an exclusive & eye-catching presentation box produced from used plastic bottles. Only chemically inert recycled plastic waste was selected as part of the process. The box is created in 4 steps: • Use plastic bottles are collected.

• The plastic bottles are then shredded into small pieces.

• The pieces are selectively hand arranged & then pressed into a panel. The hand selection & positioning of the various colored bottle makes each panel unique.

• Finally the panels are cut to size & assembled as the outer shell of the Oris Ocean Trilogy presentation box .

Oris Blue Whale 01 743 7734 4185-Set: • Case diameter: 45.50mm

• Case back: Special engraving with Blue Whale image.

• Crown: screw down.

• Bezel: Blue ceramic with diving scale.

• Dial: Gradient blue dial, applied hour markers with luminous fill, hands with luminous fill.

• Water resistance: 500m.

• Features: Chronograph function, small seconds sub-dial at 9 o'clock, date window at 4.30 o'clock.

• Movement: Oris caliber 771 (base SW 510), beats at 28,800 vph, contains 27 jewels & has a power reserve of +/- 48 hours.

Oris Great Barrier Reef III 01 743 7734 4185-Set: • Case diameter: 43.50mm

• Case back: Special engraving with Blue Whale image.

• Crown: screw down.

• Bezel: Blue ceramic with diving scale.

• Dial: Gradient blue dial, applied hour markers with luminous fill, hands with luminous fill.

• Water resistance: 300m.

• Features: Central date indicator hand.

• Movement: Oris caliber 743 (base SW 220-1), beats at 28,800 vph, contains 28 jewels & has a power reserve of +/- 38 hours.

Oris Clean Ocean 01 733 7732 4185-Set: • Case diameter: 39.50mm

• Case back: Special engraving with medallion made of recycled PET plastics set into the case back.

• Crown: screw down.

• Bezel: Blue ceramic with diving scale.

• Dial: Gradient blue dial, applied hour markers with luminous fill, hands with luminous fill.

• Water resistance: 300m.

• Features: Date window at 6 o'clock.

• Movement: Oris caliber 733 (base SW 200-1), beats at 28,800 vph, contains 26 jewels & has a power reserve of +/- 38 hours.

5230P
size:
Excellent condition New Old Stock.




History: Heir to the famous Patek Philippe Universal Time watches launched in the 1930s - and which have become cult models for frequent travelers and collectors - the reference 5230 was introduced in 2016.




For the first time, Patek Philippe is presenting this cosmopolitan timepiece in a platinum case combined with a blue dial and bracelet. The center of the dial is adorned with a new hand-guilloched circular pattern. The extra-flat self-winding 240 hu caliber, with its two rotating city and 24-hour discs, provides simultaneous and permanent time information for the world's 24 time zones.




Thanks to an ingenious mechanism patented in 1999, the user can simultaneously correct all the Universal Time displays, in one-hour increments, by simply pressing the push-button at 10 o'clock.




Watch with mechanical movement with automatic winding. Caliber 240 hu. Universal time. 24 hours and day/night indication for the 24 time zones.




Dial Blue, circular pattern hand-engraved, applied gold indexes.


Platinum case. Sapphire crystal case back. Water-resistant to 30 m. Case diameter: 38.5 mm. Thickness: 10.23 mm.




Calfskin strap, hand-sewn, navy blue. Deployment buckle.

size:
The Oyster Perpetual GMT-Master II in Oystersteel with an Oyster bracelet.





This model features a black dial and a two-colour Cerachrom bezel insert in red and blue ceramic. Designed to show the time in two different time zones simultaneously during intercontinental flights, the GMT-Master II has come to be recognized for its robustness and versatile appearance.





In addition to conventional hour, minute and seconds hands, the GMT-Master II features an arrow-tipped hand, which circles the dial once every 24 hours, as well as a bidirectional rotatable 24-hour graduated bezel. The distinctively coloured 24-hour hand displays the “home” reference time in a first time zone which can be read on the graduations on the bezel. The traveller’s local time is easily set by “jumping” from hour to hour, thanks to an ingenious mechanism operated via the winding crown: the hour hand can be adjusted forwards or backwards independently of the minute and seconds hands. This allows travellers to adapt to their new time zone without affecting the precision of their timekeeping.
